                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13157: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-27T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 27, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 27—6:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>381. Following telegram has been received from the Consul General at Hankow:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“July 26, 1 p.m. Reports are that main bodies Communists moving from
                            Maokung and Maohsien areas in Szechuan northward toward Chinghai and/or
                            Kansu. Telegraphic warning was sent yesterday to American mission
                            stations in southern Kansu. Only Americans at stations in Chinghai
                            belong to China Inland Mission. British Consulate General sent similar
                            warning through China Inland Mission on information received from
                            British Embassy. Despatch follows.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
